 General Laws c. 94, ยง 322, as amended by St. 1983, c. 96, ยง 1, HN3[
] provides, in part: "Every beverage container sold . . . 
in the commonwealth shall have a refund value of not less than five cents."

 Because we find state action immunity shields the defendants in this case, we need not discuss possible immunity under the 
Noerr-Pennington doctrine.  See United Mine Workers v. Pennington, 381 U.S. 657, 14 L. Ed. 2d 626, 85 S. Ct. 1585 (1965); 
Eastern Railroad Presidents v. Noerr Motor Freight, Inc., 365 U.S. 127, 5 L. Ed. 2d 464, 81 S. Ct. 523 (1961).
